history.content: Typically CS160 isn't too difficult to get into as a senior. 160 has a final group project and 162 is a group project based course. 160 isn't too technical in nature, it's more design principles than hardcore coding. Essentially, if you have reliable teammates, I think the workload is very manageable.

children.subject: Should be manageable as long as your teammates are reliable, and like to start relatively early. Would also recommend studying for interviews and applying (end of July/August) in the summer.
Would 162 + 160 be managable if I also want to focus on fall recruitment?

history.content:
Is 162 + 160 a bad combination in terms of workload?

I heard that I should take 162 without any other techs. The only reason I am considering 162+160 is because I REALLY want to take 160 before I graduate (I am going to be senior). If I manage to get into 160 this fall, I avoid the potential situation where I can't even get into the spring class before i graduate. But I prefer not to take a tech with 162.

Is 160 really hard to get into as a senior? For the past 2 semesters I haven't been able to get in the class. I was wondering if I will face the same problem getting into the course this fall/next spring as a senior.
history.subject: 160 enrollment and 162+160 workload?
